An exchange that sells bitcoins in bulk quantities ($1,000 worth or more).

Funding methods include:

* Cash deposit at any Bank Of America, PNC Bank, or Wells Fargo branch (16,000+ branch locations nationwide)
* Bank wire (domestic or international)

Inventory is limited.

The service operates through e-mail and only messages transmitted securely (using GPG encryption) are accepted.  

##History

The service was announced on June 12, 2012.  Bitcoins Direct is offered by Tangible Cryptography LLC, which also operates [[FastCash4Bitcoins]].

